00:19:29,399 --> 00:19:32,232
This work is Renoir's Dance
in the Country.

271
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,399
In the painting, the main character
is Renoir's friend,

272
00:19:34,482 --> 00:19:36,440
Paul and his wife-to-be...

273
00:19:36,524 --> 00:19:39,107
Maybe those two are not
the main characters of the painting?

274
00:19:42,607 --> 00:19:46,399
I mean, based on the perspective,
the lead can always change.

275
00:19:49,407 --> 00:19:50,282
Oh...

276
00:19:50,528 --> 00:19:52,898
...I'm sorry for interrupting your lesson.

277
00:20:10,273 --> 00:20:12,275
How do you do?
I'm assigned to cover this exhibit.

278
00:20:12,356 --> 00:20:15,898
The Most Korea's handsome
features editor, Kim Shinhyuk.

279
00:20:17,857 --> 00:20:19,065
Sungjoon, it's Hyejin.

280
00:20:19,315 --> 00:20:20,357
I've arrived.

281
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,940
Call me at this number when you get here.

282
00:20:36,774 --> 00:20:38,399
Five minutes left!

283
00:20:54,273 --> 00:20:56,357
Sungjoon. It's you, right?

284
00:20:58,208 --> 00:21:00,273
It's been so long!

285
00:21:01,315 --> 00:21:04,357
You... you haven't changed at all!

286
00:21:04,543 --> 00:21:05,565
Who are you?

287
00:21:08,732 --> 00:21:11,981
You're not Sungjoon...

288
00:21:12,565 --> 00:21:13,482
...Sir?

289
00:21:14,898 --> 00:21:16,065
No, I'm not!

290
00:21:16,898 --> 00:21:19,315
I'm so sorry. Sorry.

291
00:21:19,399 --> 00:21:21,190
Ma'am, why are you so strong?

292
00:21:21,399 --> 00:21:23,190
Look, I'm not old enough
to be called a ma'am.

293
00:21:25,399 --> 00:21:26,399
Whatever...

294
00:21:28,940 --> 00:21:29,981
What the...

295
00:21:32,857 --> 00:21:33,898
Hello?

296
00:21:34,399 --> 00:21:35,649
Hyejin, this is Sungjoon.

297
00:21:36,191 --> 00:21:37,525
Yes, Sungjoon.

298
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:38,981
Where are you now?

299
00:21:39,649 --> 00:21:40,984
I'm near the fountain.

300
00:21:41,065 --> 00:21:42,023
The fountain?

301
00:21:42,774 --> 00:21:44,690
I'm near the fountain, too.

302
00:21:49,753 --> 00:21:50,940
I think I've found you.

303
00:21:51,107 --> 00:21:52,107
Really?

304
00:21:52,357 --> 00:21:54,816
I don't see you anywhere.

305
00:21:55,607 --> 00:21:56,690
Don't you see me?

306
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,440
Here.

307
00:22:05,981 --> 00:22:07,273
No way.

308
00:22:19,315 --> 00:22:20,273
Kim Hyejin.

309
00:22:20,399 --> 00:22:21,565
Wait.

310
00:22:24,565 --> 00:22:26,816
In the confusion of trying to
make ends meet all the time...

311
00:22:26,897 --> 00:22:28,357
...I had forgotten one important fact!

312
00:22:28,565 --> 00:22:31,816
The image he has of me in the past...

313
00:22:31,897 --> 00:22:35,107
Sit down next to the friend
you want to get to know.

314
00:22:39,732 --> 00:22:40,857
Must be something like this.

315
00:22:41,023 --> 00:22:42,148
First prize goes to...

316
00:22:42,232 --> 00:22:44,273
...Kim Hyejin from fifth grade.

317
00:22:44,357 --> 00:22:48,649
Kim Hyejin! Kim Hyejin!

318
00:22:48,732 --> 00:22:50,690
Or maybe something like this?

319
00:22:51,399 --> 00:22:54,774
Fatty, fat boy!

320
00:22:54,897 --> 00:22:58,023
Hey, stop making fun of Sungjoon!

321
00:22:59,357 --> 00:23:02,190
That's the very least
he would expect from me!

322
00:23:04,897 --> 00:23:05,981
Are you Hyejin?

323
00:23:06,940 --> 00:23:08,232
No, I'm not.

324
00:23:08,399 --> 00:23:09,565
I'm so sorry.

325
00:23:09,649 --> 00:23:10,607
Honey.

326
00:23:10,690 --> 00:23:12,065
Hyejin, where are you?

327
00:23:28,065 --> 00:23:30,148
Wasn't that pretty server over there...

328
00:23:30,524 --> 00:23:31,860
...supposed to serve our table?

329
00:23:31,940 --> 00:23:34,148
Where is Youngmin University?

330
00:23:34,315 --> 00:23:38,232
Applicant Kim Hyejin has been rejected.

331
00:23:38,315 --> 00:23:39,940
-Rejected.
-Rejection.

332
00:23:40,023 --> 00:23:42,399
You've been rejected.

333
00:23:43,816 --> 00:23:45,565
Our home used to have a lot of money...

334
00:23:45,897 --> 00:23:49,190
...but my father lost his business
after Sungjoon moved away.

335
00:23:50,148 --> 00:23:53,649
And I used to be pretty like my mom,

336
00:23:54,065 --> 00:23:58,399
but after a while...

337
00:23:58,649 --> 00:24:03,898
...my dad's traits began to emerge
in late adolescence,

338
00:24:04,357 --> 00:24:08,148
and my looks changed over time.

339
00:24:15,897 --> 00:24:17,607
Hey. Kim Hyejin.

340
00:24:19,023 --> 00:24:21,440
Why are you back already?
Didn't you meet Fatty?

341
00:24:22,774 --> 00:24:24,023
About that...

342
00:24:28,857 --> 00:24:32,774
Let's just go home, Hari.

343
00:24:36,148 --> 00:24:37,981
If he ended up turning into a hot guy...

344
00:24:38,062 --> 00:24:39,377
...you should definitely go after him.

345
00:24:39,981 --> 00:24:41,023
Why would you run away?

346
00:24:41,190 --> 00:24:44,107
He didn't even imagine
that I'd turn out like this.

347
00:24:44,816 --> 00:24:46,716
I was right in front of him,
and he couldn't recognize me.

348
00:24:47,065 --> 00:24:51,065
There's no more trace of the pretty
Kim Hyejin that he used to know.

349
00:24:52,148 --> 00:24:55,148
I didn't want him to see me this shabby.

350
00:24:55,649 --> 00:24:57,232
I got scared.

351
00:24:57,399 --> 00:24:58,898
That's why I ran away.

352
00:24:59,607 --> 00:25:02,357
I was eager to see him again...

353
00:25:06,774 --> 00:25:08,148
...but I was too naive.

354
00:25:09,565 --> 00:25:12,440
Hey, there's nothing wrong with you!

355
00:25:12,524 --> 00:25:14,232
Girl, you're a good catch!

356
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:15,357
Just meet him.

357
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:16,816
If he asks me what I do,

358
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:18,981
do I tell him I'm unemployed at 30?

359
00:25:19,336 --> 00:25:20,795
If he says he couldn't recognize me,

360
00:25:21,315 --> 00:25:22,816
do I apologize for looking like this?

361
00:25:23,232 --> 00:25:24,107
Hey...

362
00:25:24,190 --> 00:25:28,023
I want to preserve
the memory of my first love.

363
00:25:28,981 --> 00:25:30,607
If I don't meet him,

364
00:25:30,816 --> 00:25:34,732
he'll keep those great memories of me.

365
00:25:35,273 --> 00:25:36,357
Kim Hyejin.

366
00:25:38,148 --> 00:25:39,649
You're being ridiculous.

367
00:25:40,315 --> 00:25:42,190
And you're talking like an idiot.

368
00:25:42,273 --> 00:25:43,857
Go and meet him now!

369
00:25:44,190 --> 00:25:46,148
He's a nice guy,
so he'll seem glad to see me.

370
00:25:46,565 --> 00:25:48,273
But I bet he'll feel
uncomfortable inside.

371
00:25:48,732 --> 00:25:50,482
"She's gone."

372
00:25:50,816 --> 00:25:53,273
"The girl that I once loved is gone."

373
00:25:53,649 --> 00:25:54,857
That's what he'll think.

374
00:25:55,816 --> 00:25:56,732
Hey, come on.

375
00:25:56,897 --> 00:26:01,690
I wish I could borrow
your body and face for today.

376
00:26:03,023 --> 00:26:04,148
Wait, Hari.

377
00:26:04,857 --> 00:26:07,107
I've just thought of something...

378
00:26:08,607 --> 00:26:11,148
...and I think you can help me.

379
00:26:26,774 --> 00:26:28,232
Sungjoon.

380
00:26:34,898 --> 00:26:37,190
Kim Hyejin?

381
00:26:38,857 --> 00:26:39,940
You must be Hyejin.

382
00:26:40,690 --> 00:26:42,690
Sorry I'm late.

383
00:26:44,732 --> 00:26:45,897
It's been a while.

384
00:26:46,690 --> 00:26:47,897
Have you been well?

385
00:26:52,857 --> 00:26:53,857
Hyejin.

386
00:27:28,940 --> 00:27:32,065
I've missed you, Kim Hyejin.

387
00:27:38,399 --> 00:27:39,649
Hey, kid!

388
00:27:40,690 --> 00:27:41,898
Did you move here?

389
00:27:41,981 --> 00:27:45,148
My best friend Hari used to live here.

390
00:27:45,897 --> 00:27:48,568
I'm in the fifth grade, what about you?

391
00:27:48,649 --> 00:27:50,482
Third grade, fourth grade?

392
00:27:56,897 --> 00:27:58,774
Hey, kid!

393
00:28:01,857 --> 00:28:03,315
Will everyone welcome our new student?

394
00:28:03,399 --> 00:28:05,440
His name is Ji Sungjoon,
and he just transferred here.

395
00:28:05,898 --> 00:28:07,981
Hey, kid! You're not a kid?

396
00:28:08,065 --> 00:28:09,482
She called him a kid!

397
00:28:10,816 --> 00:28:12,981
That's not a kid. It's a fatty!

398
00:28:25,898 --> 00:28:27,607
My mom asked me to give this to you.

399
00:28:28,190 --> 00:28:32,190
And sorry, I thought
you were younger than me.

400
00:28:32,690 --> 00:28:34,357
You should've told me that you weren't.

401
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:39,816
Are you working on a puzzle?

402
00:28:41,190 --> 00:28:42,857
I saw that painting in a textbook!

403
00:28:44,190 --> 00:28:46,649
There's someone here in the corner.

404
00:28:48,023 --> 00:28:49,232
You found her.

405
00:28:50,023 --> 00:28:52,232
That girl is hiding.

406
00:28:53,524 --> 00:28:54,565
Hiding?

407
00:28:55,107 --> 00:28:57,148
She really does look like she's hiding.

408
00:28:57,981 --> 00:28:59,357
I wonder what she's looking at?

409
00:28:59,981 --> 00:29:02,649
Maybe she wants to
dance on the stage, too?

410
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:07,897
In my opinion, she's watching the man...

411
00:29:08,315 --> 00:29:09,940
...because she secretly likes him.

412
00:29:10,482 --> 00:29:12,190
That could be true, too.

413
00:29:12,774 --> 00:29:15,232
She's hidden,
so it's kind of like a picture puzzle.

414
00:29:16,107 --> 00:29:17,940
A picture puzzle?

415
00:29:18,981 --> 00:29:21,981
Look. You couldn't find her unless
you were really searching for her.

416
00:29:22,065 --> 00:29:23,440
Like a picture puzzle.

417
00:29:24,482 --> 00:29:25,357
You're right.

418
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:27,482
It really is like a picture puzzle.

419
00:29:29,898 --> 00:29:32,190
I didn't want to disappoint
my first love.

420
00:29:33,565 --> 00:29:38,315
I refused to end up like a piece
of popcorn in front of my first love.

421
00:29:40,190 --> 00:29:43,524
So eventually, I just...

422
00:29:44,690 --> 00:29:50,565
...watched him as I hid
from his surroundings.

423
00:29:54,107 --> 00:29:56,148
Don't make any mistakes
and do as we planned.

424
00:29:59,107 --> 00:30:00,440
Here is our menu.

425
00:30:04,232 --> 00:30:05,524
Should we go ahead and order?

426
00:30:06,107 --> 00:30:06,981
Okay.

427
00:30:12,897 --> 00:30:14,690
Would you like to place an order?

428
00:30:16,732 --> 00:30:17,690
Miss?

429
00:30:18,607 --> 00:30:19,565
Miss.

430
00:30:20,399 --> 00:30:21,273
What?

431
00:30:22,399 --> 00:30:23,607
Would you like to place an order?

432
00:30:26,898 --> 00:30:27,860
Give me this, this one.

433
00:30:27,940 --> 00:30:30,607
The grilled shrimp and caviar
with the filet mignon steak.

434
00:30:30,690 --> 00:30:31,690
Coming right up.

435
00:30:31,774 --> 00:30:32,690
Okay.

436
00:30:33,607 --> 00:30:34,482
No!

437
00:30:35,065 --> 00:30:38,607
Forget the filet mignon steak
and give me a cup of coffee.

438
00:30:38,857 --> 00:30:41,232
-Coffee.
-Sure.

439
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:47,065
I don't know what to ask you first.

440
00:30:47,897 --> 00:30:49,440
I have so many questions.

441
00:30:52,273 --> 00:30:53,315
What about work?

442
00:30:53,690 --> 00:30:54,857
What kind of work do you do?

443
00:30:55,065 --> 00:30:57,357
When he asks you what you do,
tell him this.

444
00:30:57,732 --> 00:30:58,940
I'm still studying.

445
00:30:59,399 --> 00:31:02,482
I think I was meant to study.

446
00:31:03,065 --> 00:31:04,607
So you're still in school?

447
00:31:05,023 --> 00:31:05,898
What about you?

448
00:31:06,107 --> 00:31:09,732
I'm involved in art directing.

449
00:31:10,565 --> 00:31:12,565
I have no idea what that is.

450
00:31:12,690 --> 00:31:14,897
Oh, I see.

451
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:16,981
Are your parents doing well?

452
00:31:17,357 --> 00:31:18,273
Of course.

453
00:31:18,357 --> 00:31:19,649
My mom and dad are doing...

454
00:31:20,190 --> 00:31:21,273
Well!

455
00:31:24,897 --> 00:31:28,524
They're both doing well.

456
00:31:31,190 --> 00:31:32,232
Are you okay?

457
00:31:41,107 --> 00:31:43,357
Are your parents doing well, too?

458
00:31:44,315 --> 00:31:47,940
My father is in Seattle,
and I was in New York for work.

459
00:31:48,649 --> 00:31:52,065
I don't see him often,
but he's doing well as always.

460
00:31:52,774 --> 00:31:53,981
What about your mother?

461
00:31:57,774 --> 00:31:58,774
What?

462
00:32:03,732 --> 00:32:05,148
His mother passed away.

463
00:32:09,940 --> 00:32:11,565
Oh, gosh.

464
00:32:13,232 --> 00:32:14,816
Your father...

465
00:32:15,524 --> 00:32:18,898
I thought he might've remarried.

466
00:32:20,816 --> 00:32:22,399
Oh, okay.

467
00:32:23,357 --> 00:32:24,440
Yes, he did remarry.

468
00:32:24,816 --> 00:32:26,148
It's been about seven years now.

469
00:32:26,524 --> 00:32:29,273
I had a feeling that he did,
which is why I'm asking.

470
00:32:31,690 --> 00:32:35,565
But why did you decide to contact me
all of a sudden?

471
00:32:38,315 --> 00:32:40,981
I was cleaning up my place
before I came back to Korea...

472
00:32:41,399 --> 00:32:42,897
...and I found a box.

473
00:32:43,399 --> 00:32:45,232
I didn't know I still had them,

474
00:32:45,816 --> 00:32:48,482
but I found the letters
that you used to write me.

475
00:32:48,981 --> 00:32:52,273
It reminded me of our childhood...

476
00:32:52,897 --> 00:32:55,898
...and I wanted to reunite with you.

477
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:57,482
I see.

478
00:32:58,357 --> 00:33:01,232
Why did you stop contacting me back then?

479
00:33:01,607 --> 00:33:04,732
If he asks why I stopped
contacting him, tell him this.

480
00:33:05,232 --> 00:33:09,774
After you left the country,
we also left to Japan.

481
00:33:10,315 --> 00:33:12,732
But then I lost your address.

482
00:33:13,774 --> 00:33:15,940
I was curious about you, too.

483
00:33:16,897 --> 00:33:18,857
It's nice to finally meet you again.

484
00:33:19,732 --> 00:33:21,399
And so the mystery is solved.

485
00:33:22,524 --> 00:33:25,440
My letters kept being returned to me,
so I was wondering what happened.

486
00:33:26,399 --> 00:33:27,897
I see.

487
00:33:28,023 --> 00:33:30,898
Do you remember the puzzle back then?
It was in the box, too.

488
00:33:31,482 --> 00:33:33,940
Puzzle?

489
00:33:35,273 --> 00:33:37,649
Oh, the puzzle...

490
00:33:38,857 --> 00:33:39,940
Oh, that.

491
00:33:46,273 --> 00:33:47,482
"The hidden girl"

492
00:33:48,357 --> 00:33:49,440
Are you all right?

493
00:33:49,897 --> 00:33:53,774
"The hidden girl" Oh, the hidden girl!

494
00:33:56,065 --> 00:33:57,315
You remember?

495
00:34:00,357 --> 00:34:02,857
I had forgotten that I had it...

496
00:34:03,399 --> 00:34:07,440
...but then remembered
that we used to put it together.

497
00:34:08,524 --> 00:34:09,898
I felt thankful.

498
00:34:12,107 --> 00:34:16,482
Until I met you, I was always alone.

499
00:34:17,649 --> 00:34:20,315
But I realized something
when you became my friend.

500
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:26,607
That even if you have
just one friend in the world...

501
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,565
...you won't be lonely.

502
00:34:30,607 --> 00:34:32,232
That life could be fun.

503
00:34:33,940 --> 00:34:38,357
I was glad you were my friend, Hyejin.

504
00:34:40,732 --> 00:34:45,148
I was happy that I had
such a great friend like you.

505
00:34:47,565 --> 00:34:52,774
Then I became thankful,
and I started to miss you.

506
00:34:54,482 --> 00:34:55,898
So I started looking for you.

507
00:35:00,190 --> 00:35:01,565
Now that I'm here,

508
00:35:02,774 --> 00:35:04,524
I think I've made the right choice.

509
00:35:15,940 --> 00:35:20,440
I think I've made the right choice too.

510
00:35:27,273 --> 00:35:28,816
I'll drop you off where you live.

511
00:35:29,399 --> 00:35:30,981
It's okay. I drove here, too.

512
00:35:32,023 --> 00:35:33,065
Really?

513
00:35:34,482 --> 00:35:38,357
Then I guess we'll part ways for today.

514
00:35:38,816 --> 00:35:39,690
Sungjoon.

515
00:35:40,774 --> 00:35:42,148
I have something to tell you.

516
00:35:43,065 --> 00:35:48,357
To preserve our precious memories,
and bring this night to a beautiful end,

517
00:35:48,981 --> 00:35:50,273
tell him this.

518
00:35:50,607 --> 00:35:53,273
I'm going overseas for school.

519
00:35:54,315 --> 00:35:55,190
What?

520
00:35:55,273 --> 00:35:58,107
I regret having to tell you this
on our reunion,

521
00:35:58,482 --> 00:36:00,232
but I've been preparing to go overseas.

522
00:36:02,940 --> 00:36:06,357
Oh, I see.

523
00:36:07,565 --> 00:36:08,607
Where are you going?

524
00:36:10,107 --> 00:36:10,981
What?

525
00:36:12,732 --> 00:36:13,899
"Great Britain's Magician of Light"

526
00:36:14,524 --> 00:36:16,424
"Great Britain's Magician of Light"
To the United Kingdom.

527
00:36:17,065 --> 00:36:18,148
I'm going to the UK.

528
00:36:19,981 --> 00:36:21,273
When are you leaving?

529
00:36:21,981 --> 00:36:23,482
-Tomorrow.
-Tomorrow?

530
00:36:23,690 --> 00:36:24,897
Yes, tomorrow.

531
00:36:25,148 --> 00:36:26,148
Tomorrow?

532
00:36:31,897 --> 00:36:34,357
What am I going to do now?

533
00:36:36,232 --> 00:36:38,357
It feels too early
to part ways like this.

534
00:36:39,897 --> 00:36:41,607
We'll contact each other again.

535
00:36:42,357 --> 00:36:43,273
Okay.

536
00:36:44,399 --> 00:36:48,148
I go to London a couple of
times a year for work,

537
00:36:48,649 --> 00:36:50,732
so I guess I'll see you then.

538
00:36:51,232 --> 00:36:52,482
Good luck there.

539
00:36:54,357 --> 00:36:56,107
And keep in touch.

540
00:36:57,273 --> 00:36:59,482
